<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>cotton on to someone • cotton up to someone</xh5><p> <i>cotton on to someone</i>—(coll., also: cotton to someone) become attached to smb.; come to like a person: I suppose the fact of the matter was that she didn’t <u>cotton on to</u> me.</p><p> <i>cotton up to someone</i>—(coll.) try to start a friendship with a person: I saw you <u>cottoning up to</u> the new student; was he friendly?</p> </entry>
